channel.title: Silabsoft client failure
channel.description:
Ok so i've been using silabsoft for about a month now no problem, but all of a sudden about 3 days ago i got this error.... Sorry, an error has occurred whilst loading runescape
To fix try the following(in order):
1:Try closing all open web-browser windows, and reloading
2:Try clearing all your web-browser cache from tools-> internet options
3:Try using a different game-world
4:Try rebooting your computer
5:Try selecting a different version of java from the play-game menu
I have tried all that and tried deleting the client twice and redownloading and i still get the same problem. That error is displayed on the actual game window, not the cmd window.
The error i get on the cmd window is...
Error:loaderror unpacking config 86
Please help!
